<tr>
<td class="navbox-abovebelow" colspan="2">
<div>Legend:
<p>(federal) = federal holidays, (state) = state holidays, (religious) = religious holidays, (week) = weeklong holidays, (month) = monthlong holidays, (36) = <a href="/wiki/Title_36_of_the_United_States_Code" title="Title 36 of the United States Code">Title 36 Observances and Ceremonies</a><br />
<b>Bolded</b> text indicates major holidays that are commonly celebrated by Americans, which often represent the major celebrations of the month.<a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.usa.gov/citizens/holidays.shtml">[1]</a><a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.immihelp.com/newcomer/major-holidays-festivals-america.html">[2]</a><br /></p>
See also: <a href="/wiki/Lists_of_holidays" title="Lists of holidays">Lists of holidays</a>, <a href="/wiki/Hallmark_holiday" title="Hallmark holiday">Hallmark holidays</a>, public holidays in the <a href="/wiki/Public_holidays_in_the_United_States" title="Public holidays in the United States">United States</a>, <a href="/wiki/Public_holidays_in_Puerto_Rico" title="Public holidays in Puerto Rico">Puerto Rico</a>, <a href="/wiki/Public_holidays_in_the_United_States_Virgin_Islands" title="Public holidays in the United States Virgin Islands">United States Virgin Islands</a>, <a href="/wiki/State_holidays_in_New_Jersey" title="State holidays in New Jersey">New Jersey</a> and <a href="/wiki/New_York_State_government_holidays" title="New York State government holidays">New York</a>.</div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>


